IT Budget




Spectrum Brands is a global consumer products company and a leading supplier of batteries, portable lighting, lawn and garden products, household insect control, shaving and grooming products, personal care products and specialty pet supplies. Spectrum Brands' products are available in… MoreSpectrum Brands is a global consumer products company and a leading supplier of batteries, portable lighting, lawn and garden products, household insect control, shaving and grooming products, personal care products and specialty pet supplies. Spectrum Brands' products are available in more than one million stores in 120 countries around the world.
The Chief Information Officer heads the IT department of Spectrum Brands, Inc, located in Madison, WI. He oversees the North America data center, which supports business entities that constitute about two-thirds of revenue. The Director of IT Infrastructure helps oversees these… MoreThe Chief Information Officer heads the IT department of Spectrum Brands, Inc, located in Madison, WI. He oversees the North America data center, which supports business entities that constitute about two-thirds of revenue. The Director of IT Infrastructure helps oversees these data center operations and manages the security systems that support the enterprise architecture.

The IT department provides a lot of support to the company's business goals. Systems architects in the IT group work with people on the business side to improve their operating environment. After consulting with the marketing department, the Manager of Applications Design oversees application implementation and directs IT projects to satisfy their business partners. A manager is responsible for information and network security at the company.

Spectrum Brands, Inc. has led initiatives areas of data protection and recovery software archiving, and software storage infrastructure.

Spectrum Brands, Inc. describes new data implementations as its biggest storage headache.

Its top storage pain points are being routinely outside the backup window, the need for better and more reliable off-site disaster recovery, and the lack of modernizing/virtualizing solutions for systems and tape that are no longer viable.

Spectrum Brands, Inc. uses CA ARCserver (80%) and Symantec NetBackup (20%) as its main backup application. Its daily and weekly total data backup is 40TB and 100TB respectively, with a >8 hours backup window. Its backup growth is around 30TB. Relating to its remote locations, data is backed up locally, and some remote locations have WAN optimization deployed.

The IT budget is typically finalized in Q3.





